definition.value: A biaryl that is phenol which is substituted at position 2 by a 1,3,4-oxadiazol-2-yl group. Formerly used as a hypnotic drug.
The organic sodium salt of hexacyclonic acid. It is a CNS stimulant.
An amphetamine methylated on nitrogen and with the phenyl ring methoxylated at C-2. A beta-adrenergic receptor agonist, it is used as a bronchodilator.
An N-acylurea in which the acyl substituent is 2-ethyl-3-methylpentanoyl. A monoureide sedative, it has a duration of hypnotic effect similar to that of the short-acting barbiturates.
The bromide salt of pentamethonium. It is a ganglion blocker and exhibits antihypertensive activity.
